snippet.title: Bing Weather
snippet.description: Bing Weather is well worth the free download for its pretty, dead-simple design and comprehensive weather reports.

snippet.title: Yahoo Weather
snippet.description: With an elegant interface, weather information, and interactive maps, Yahoo Weather is a must-have for weather watchers everywhere.

snippet.title: Verykool RS90 Vortex (unlocked)
snippet.description: At $280, the Vortex is a good deal for a rugged phone, but those looking for a high-end Android phone should look elsewhere.

snippet.title: Minutely for Android
snippet.description: While Minutely's crowdsourced weather data is certainly a brilliant idea, it still needs an updated interface and more users to be considered a go-to source for weather information.

snippet.title: NOAA Hi-Def Radar
snippet.description: NOAA Hi-Def Radar is an excellent way to track storms, giving you a ton of useful information, but it's missing one important feature.

snippet.title: Weather Channel, DirecTV end months-long tempest
snippet.description: Weather Channel returns to lineup after agreeing to reduce amount of reality TV programming it offers -- a sticking point for the satellite provider. There's no word, though, on whether DirecTV in turn agrees to pay a higher fee.

snippet.title: Songza tunes into Weather Channel data for music selection
snippet.description: A new partnership means you could hear Burt Bacharach crooning in your ear when raindrops start falling on your head.

snippet.title: Fujifilm FinePix S1
snippet.description: Sure, it'll capture 16-megapixel pictures and HD video, but what's important is where it can do it and from how far away.

snippet.title: South Korea to banish bloatware from smartphones
snippet.description: Phone makers and carriers, take notice: You'll have to let smartphone owners delete all that software you stuff into handsets that no one actually wants.

snippet.title: North Korea names space agency 'NADA,' mimics NASA logo
snippet.description: North Korea's newly named space agency sports the unfortunate acronym "NADA" and features a familiar-looking logo.
